The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, March 28: The Reserve Bank of India will announce the Annual Policy for 2005-06 on April 28. The central bank governor Y. V. Reddy will meet the chief executives of commercial banks to unveil the monetary and credit policy for the next fiscal, a Reserve Bank spokesperson said.

 New Delhi, March 28: The ministry of company affairs and Sebi has stepped up efforts to trace vanishing companies and have filed first information reports against 104 such fly-by-night operators. ?For tracing whereabouts of the vanishing companies, the matter has been taken up with the concerned passport offices and other authorities,? an official release said today.

 New Delhi, March 28: Indra Nooyi, president and chief financial officer of PepsiCo, is in India on a business visit to discuss the future direction of the company?s operations here. 

 New Delhi, March 28: The government may not revise petrol and diesel prices on April 1 as petroleum minister Mani Shankar Aiyar will be in Saudi Arabia for the next three days.

 New Delhi, March 28: With marine hull insurance going out of the administered regime from next month, the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority has issued new norms for marine and war risk covers.




